---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service - Gas Town Hall"
  description="Terms of Service for Gas Town Hall website and community."
>
  <div class="terms-page">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: January 2026</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
      <p>
        By accessing and using Gas Town Hall (gastownhall.ai), you agree to be
        bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms,
        please do not use this website.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Description of Service</h2>
      <p>
        Gas Town Hall provides documentation, resources, and community access
        for Gas Town, an open source orchestration layer for AI coding agents.
        The website includes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Technical documentation</li>
        <li>Blog posts and articles</li>
        <li>Links to community resources (Discord, GitHub, X)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Open Source License</h2>
      <p>
        Gas Town and its documentation are open source projects. The specific
        license terms for the Gas Town software can be found in the <a
          href="https://github.com/steveyegge/gastown"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">Gas Town GitHub repository</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>User Conduct</h2>
      <p>
        When participating in Gas Town Hall community spaces (Discord, GitHub,
        etc.), you agree to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Be respectful and constructive in all interactions</li>
        <li>Not post spam, malware, or malicious content</li>
        <li>Not harass, threaten, or abuse other community members</li>
        <li>Not impersonate others or misrepresent your affiliation</li>
        <li>
          Follow the specific guidelines of each platform (Discord Terms, GitHub
          Terms, etc.)
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        The Gas Town Hall website design, branding, and original content are the
        property of their respective creators. The technical documentation is
        part of the open source Gas Town project and is subject to its license.
      </p>
      <p>
        Third-party trademarks, logos, and brand names appearing on this site
        are the property of their respective owners.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        Gas Town Hall and all related documentation and software are provided
        "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied. We make no
        warranties regarding:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>The accuracy or completeness of information on this site</li>
        <li>The availability or uninterrupted operation of the website</li>
        <li>The fitness of Gas Town software for any particular purpose</li>
        <li>The security or safety of any code or content</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, Gas Town Hall and its creators
        shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special,
        consequential, or punitive damages arising from your use of or inability
        to use the website or any related software.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Third-Party Links</h2>
      <p>
        This website contains links to third-party websites and services
        (GitHub, Discord, X, Medium, etc.). We are not responsible for the
        content, privacy policies, or practices of these external sites.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Modifications</h2>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to modify these Terms of Service at any time.
        Changes will be effective immediately upon posting to this page. Your
        continued use of the website after changes constitutes acceptance of the
        modified terms.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about these Terms of Service, contact us at <a
          href="mailto:gastownhall@gmail.com">gastownhall@gmail.com</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .terms-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  ul {
    margin: 0.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--color-link);
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
</style>
